<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="584" pageId="4" pageNumber="583" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1805,2010]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="584" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,373,1805,1830]" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Body length, 1.6–1.7 mm. Wing length, 1.4 mm, width, 0.5 mm. 
<emphasis box="[1127,1196,1805,1830]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Head.</emphasis>
Frons dark brown to black, with violet reflections; antenna mostly brown, arista-like stylus (
<figureCitation box="[958,1026,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,376,1328]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,375,1328]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Heads of males of new species in the Chrysotus longipalpus species group. 1. Chrysotus plumarista sp. nov., dorsolateral view; inset shows male arista. 2. Chrysotus mystax sp. nov., anterior view. 3. Chrysotus mccreadiei sp. nov., anterior view.4. Chrysotus keyensis sp.nov.; a. anterodorsal view; b. lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1206906/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, inset) with distal fifth very slightly broadened, feathered and white at apex; face yellow, essentially obliterated by eyes near middle; proboscis yellowbrown with pale setae; palpus (
<figureCitation box="[509,575,1913,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,376,1328]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,375,1328]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Heads of males of new species in the Chrysotus longipalpus species group. 1. Chrysotus plumarista sp. nov., dorsolateral view; inset shows male arista. 2. Chrysotus mystax sp. nov., anterior view. 3. Chrysotus mccreadiei sp. nov., anterior view.4. Chrysotus keyensis sp.nov.; a. anterodorsal view; b. lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1206906/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) white, shiny, bare except small medioapical seta, roundish with inner and apical edge nearly straight, apical edge minutely fringed (ratio tibia I: palpus, 23:12) (
<collectionCode box="[1109,1190,1950,1974]" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">MSSC</collectionCode>
). 
<emphasis box="[1207,1296,1949,1974]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="583">Thorax.</emphasis>
Mesonotum and scutellum metallic green with violet reflections; mesopleuron brown with some bluish reflections and some pruinosity. 
<emphasis box="[276,340,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Wing.</emphasis>
Halter yellow, calypter brownish. Legs. I: 22, 23, 12, 5, 4, 2, 
<date box="[1023,1074,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">2. II</date>
: 25, 28, 14, 6, 4, 3, 
<date box="[1290,1350,152,176]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">2. III</date>
: 29, 32, 8, 8, 5, 3, 2. Legs yellow except all coxae and base of femur I brown; apical tarsomeres only very slightly darkened. Setae on coxae I, II, and III brown. Hypopygium brown, not dissected; cercus yellow, short, with some brown hairs. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[219,313,260,285]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="584" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,295,320]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from the Latin 
<emphasis box="[676,746,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">pluma</emphasis>
(feathery) + arista, in reference to the slightly broadened and feathered apex of the arista in males (
<figureCitation box="[570,636,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,376,1328]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,375,1328]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Heads of males of new species in the Chrysotus longipalpus species group. 1. Chrysotus plumarista sp. nov., dorsolateral view; inset shows male arista. 2. Chrysotus mystax sp. nov., anterior view. 3. Chrysotus mccreadiei sp. nov., anterior view.4. Chrysotus keyensis sp.nov.; a. anterodorsal view; b. lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1206906/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
