<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="584" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,151,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,548,573]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Remarks.</emphasis>
This is the only known species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Aldrich" authorityYear="1896" box="[738,902,548,573]" class="Insecta" family="Dolichopodidae" genus="Chrysotus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="584" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longipalpus">
<emphasis box="[738,902,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">C. longipalpus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group with a modified arista (
<figureCitation box="[1238,1303,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1349,1372]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,376,1328]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[166,1421,375,1328]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Heads of males of new species in the Chrysotus longipalpus species group. 1. Chrysotus plumarista sp. nov., dorsolateral view; inset shows male arista. 2. Chrysotus mystax sp. nov., anterior view. 3. Chrysotus mccreadiei sp. nov., anterior view.4. Chrysotus keyensis sp.nov.; a. anterodorsal view; b. lateral view. Scale bar = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1206906/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
, inset). The antennae are missing in the 
<typeStatus box="[463,563,584,608]" pageId="5" pageNumber="584">paratype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
